Really any rubber seals. They get a set to the oil and a switch distrubes 
this. It is like mixing chemicals. you can mix 2 with no proble but add a 
3rd and you get a reaction. Same with syn and petro oils. if you mix the two 
together your oil will turn to goo. They just don't mix and the rubber is 
porous so it takes in both and the reaction is that the rubber goes south. 
Gets soft and leaks. because seals get a set to an oil and if you change 
that it is gonna leak.

Bob









